events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard made three free throws with one second remaining for the final margin, and the Portland Trail Blazers survived a wild finish to beat the short-handed Miami Heat 125-122 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: McCollum, Blazers hold off short-handed Heat, 125-122

events.name: Washington Wizards at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Alec Burks scored 15 of his 27 points in the fourth quarter and the New York Knicks beat the Washington Wizards 106-102 on Thursday night to sweep the two-game set.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks storm back, complete sweep of Wizards 106-102

events.name: LA Clippers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Reggie Jackson scored 28 points, Paul George had 24 points and 13 rebounds and the short-handed Los Angeles Clippers rallied in the second half to beat the San Antonio Spurs 98-85 on Thursday night for their fourth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, George lead short-handed Clippers past Spurs, 98-85

headlines.description: — Danny Green hit eight 3-pointers and scored 28 points against his former team, and the Philadelphia 76ers weathered Los Angeles' late rally for their fourth straight victory, 109-101 over the slumping Lakers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Danny Green lights up Lakers for 28, Sixers win 109-101

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — De’Aaron Fox had a career-best 44 points and the Sacramento Kings beat the short-handed Golden State Warriors 141-119 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fox scores career-high 44, Kings roll past Warriors 141-119
